Name me one copy-protection scheme which ISN'T annoying.  Besides, I don't think you fully understand the way the system works, because even though you are required to reactivate after you change one of the key hardware pieces (not the hard drive), you can still run the OS for a limited time before reactivation.  I know this was discussed at length at some of the hardware benchmarking sites who were concerned about this exact issue, so maybe I can dig up a link if you're really interested.<br>
<br>
<b><i>Every version of Office has bugs </b></i><br>
<br>
The following is a complete list of bug-free software introduced in the past 10 years:<br>
<br>
