<br>
On the other hand, Microsoft has one of the best automated update utilities on the Internet.  Far more useful to me than those manuals I always threw away.<br>
<br>
<b><i>Do I use Microsoft products? Yes, unless there is a viable alternative. In most cases there isn't a viable alternative though, because they've run the competition out of business through their tactics. </b></i><br>
<br>
You use the term "viable alternative" in the abstract, but realistically, what specific "viable alternatives" were there which were (a) better than the Microsoft product and (b) run out of business by Microsoft?  In other words, what product did you use in the past, but can't use now solely because Microsoft doesn't allow you to? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueridalafar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eridalafar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/2/01 7:09:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More bug stuff</span><hr size=1> Tudamorf  say:<br>
